      • maybeQuestionSetAvailable

        boolean maybeQuestionSetAvailable(LookupRoot container,
                                  java.util.Date referenceDate,
                                  Offering offering)
        Check availability without running availability script. Used by webservice where no actual entity can be created
        Parameters:
        container - the look up root
        referenceDate - the date to look up
        offering - the offering
        Returns:
        true is question set may be available
        See Also:
        isQuestionSetAvailable(entity.AnswerContainer)

      • isQuestionSetAvailable

        boolean isQuestionSetAvailable(AnswerContainer container)
        Returns true if this QuestionSet is available. All of the following conditions must be satisfied:
        • The "container" argument is not null
        • This QuestionSet is available according to its lookup table and script
        • If an offering is selected on the container's associated PolicyPeriod, then this QuestionSet must be enabled in the offering.
        • All QuestionSetFilters for this QuestionSet pass
        Parameters:
        container - The AnswerContainer which is to hold the responses to this QuestionSet
        Returns:
        true if this QuestionSet is available, false otherwise

      • getOrderedQuestions

        Question[] getOrderedQuestions()
        Returns the questions ordered first according to priority and then according to public id. This method will sort the questions each and every time they are pulled, so if you are worried about performance use the method getQuestions() instead.
        Returns:
        The questions in this question set ordered by priority and public id.
